body:
I went rather quickly on this mornings trip, however the travel time hasn’t really changed.

Hudson’s Coffee Shop ran out of lactose-free milk, so I had to go across the street to the “Under the Clock” cafe instead.
When I walked down to Hudsons this afternoon, there was s sign on the door announcing that they had to close early; back to UTC!
Catching the bus because it’s supposed to rain this morning. Anyway, the roads are wet so more dangerous to ride the scooter.
Bus delayed due to a bus that was broken down at Buranda blocking the busway to all other buses!

Working from home today as there is no Steering Committee meeting this week. Anita has taken Katherine to her Orthodontal appointment this morning and they are going to the Japanese Restaurant at Upper Mt Gravatt afterwards.

Stopped for Coffee and a shared toastie. The place was crazy busy with long queues, especially the petrol line.

The Veterans MC were out in the carpark. Most were fairly young so veterans are now from other conflicts.
We sat in the shade near the BP chargers to have the coffee. I got the camping chairs out to sit on.
Stopped to go to the toilet and clean all the sap and nectar off the bonnet and windscreen. Don’t park under Silky Oaks in spring!!
We noticed the large body of water on the Tesla Navigation map as we drove through Landsborough so decided to go and have a look. Very nice place for a picnic and there weren’t many people there.
We went for a short walk along the boardwalk and a little further. Anita has a broken toe and needs to wear a ‘Moon’ shoe to protect it.
The planned destination for this trip was the Endeavour Prize Home at Yandina. It was one of the best prize homes I’ve inspected in years, with multimillion dollar views of the coast.

Charged the Tesla at one of the supercharger stations for 7 minutes from 44% to 60%. Then I moved over to one of the Tesla AC connectors and starting charging there.

We went in to the ‘Ginger Factory’ for lunch. I had a chicken burger without the mayonnaise and a Mexican soft drink.

The chicken burger got to me. Even though they didn’t include the mayonnaise as requested, the chicken had been marinated in something spicey. 

The public toilets near the railway station are really well maintained!
We stopped at the BP station for a quick break, and coffee. Their coffee tastes terrible and needed almost two sugars to improve it.
That’s wierd? We were at the club for hours, but the time has gone missing
I was going to ride the scooter to work, but the  front tyre was flat! I was too late to swap over to the other scooter, so I alerted Sean who was able to get the sleep computers restarted.

Dropped Katherine off at Griffith University. She has a presentation to give for a uni subject.

I have a meeting at 11:00am and I was tempted to stay at the hospital, but that would have cost too much in parking fees.
I bought a ham, cheese and tomato sandwich and coffee on the way home.
Dropped Katherine off for QYO rehearsals. It’s a long busy day for her.
It’s QYO auditions and Katherine is also helping out.
We drove to Wilston for coffee. It was busy there, so we decided to order it as take-away. A penny-farthing rode by while we were waiting for the coffee.
I got out the camping chairs and we had our coffee in the shade of a large tree beside a soccer field.
There’s a toilet here
I use the ramp to get the scooter into the back of the Forester and set off for Ride Electric to get the tyre tube replaced.
The Forester was out of Petrol, so I had to make a stop at the Shell Station to fill up. It cost me just over $90.00!
The scooter mechanic offered to fix the tyre straight away, so I checked out all the bicycles while I was there.
Anita wasn’t feeling well, so stayed in the car while I went to Coles to shop for the things that are difficult to order online from Woolworths.
We parked at Garden City and waited for the shuttle to the Metro Depot
We decided to go to the club earlier and maybe have dinner there after playing. I was extremely lucky on one of the machines when I won $350.
When we got back home, Katherine was recording a presentation, so we went for a drive so that we wouldn’t disturb her.
There was a thunderstorm coming, so I was going a bit faster to stay dry. I arrived home just as it started to rain. I could hear the big drops of rain hitting the top of my helmet.
The forecast is for rain (70%) so it’s a bus trip today.
Walked down to the Nurses Station Cafe with Kiara.
Recycling our drink bottles
Coffee and Danish to takeaway.
Got out the camping chairs and chilled in the park.
Drove the WRX around the suburb to recharge the battery.
Refuelled the WRX. This tank should last a while with Anita using the Forester now.
Bought two sunshades and then discovered the missing one in seconds of returning home. It ended up that the missing shade was the best size for the Forester.
Put the car cover on the WRX
Anita wanted to go to the club early. In contrast to last weekend, I lost my gambling budget unusually rapidly.

I initially thought the physiotherapist was at the shopping centre near the railway station at Coopers Plains, but the traffic was jammed waiting to cross the railway line, so I pulled into Joyce Street and checked. Oops.
I got there too early so decided to go for a walk
Dropped Katherine off at the bus stop
Refuelling the Forester - $90
Waiting to pick Katherine up.
We went to the QYO Finale Concert at QPAC. We parked underneath in the QPAC carpark which was a mistake, because it took an hour to leave!
Renewed my prescription. I have one more repeat before I have to go back to the GP for a new script.

Anita wanted to go and sit in a park with coffee, so we headed over to the coffee shop near Toohey Forest, but it was really busy and the carpark was almost full. We then headed back towards Mt Gravatt with a revised plan to get coffee at Zaraffas and go up Mt Gravatt, but we ended up at a closer coffee shop and headed over to Holland Park instead.

I went for a 10 km ride on the bicycle for the first time since January (nine months). I enjoyed the ride along the paths we would normally walk, and will again when Anita’s broken toe heals in a few more weeks.

I saw the kingfisher in the distance over the other side of the creek, when I stopped at the condemned path to look.

I saw a tortoise sunning itself on the same log that the old water dragon usually rests. And there was another Kingfisher in the tree above.

We went to the social club for dinner. I tried their chicken and avocado burger with chips. It was excellent, although they did add a different sauce to the tomato sauce described on the menu!

I had better luck this evening compared to last week and won $50,00 for Katherine.
The weather forecast is for rain and thunderstorms in the afternoon, so it’s a bus day.
Feeling sick today! Woke up with a sore throat.
Kiara likes to have coffee at the nurses station so I go for the walk and then go to Hudson’s on the way back to the hospital.
I ordered a UBER ride to take me home. I’m feeling too unwell to catch the bus.
